  "elapsed_s": 14.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But after two years, she remarried, not believing that her husband could be still alive.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So strange stories happened in this-- in this misery, and war-torn, and-- and-- and-- and-- and suffering population of surviving Jews, as well as anybody who survives a war.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "How did we find out-- found out about my mother?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As I mentioned, life started to return and normalize in the city.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my father was starting to, again, establish himself in business.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] he was always going, he said, I'm going into a portion of the city for a newspaper's [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] editorial location, where the paper is edited.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And outside on the fence, under glass, there is always a list of people who are known to be alive from different concentrations camp, who survived.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "By then, there was obvious knowledge that many people were taken to the concentration camps and started to have people like myself who returned to tell the world what happened and where were we.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And before I tell about how we found out about my mother, I have to stop and to tell about a very sad moment when my little friend, Tomas Stern's father and mother who survived, were asking what do I know about their son.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I had to deliver the news that I know he is dead.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I-- I tell you the feeling, which I had at the time, to face somebody to tell.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I felt guilty.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I still feel guilty.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because somehow, why didn't he survived with me?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He should have.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I was luckier.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And whenever I walked in the street, on the same street where the parents of him lived, I was, whenever I notice from a distance, I was trying to avoid to face them again.",
      "word_count": 34
    }
  ],
